# View Layer Cameras

Every camera in the project must be owned by a view layer. Do not place cameras directly in scenes.

## Rule

- **All cameras** live inside view layer prefabs (e.g. `view_layer_widget`)
- **No accidental cameras** in scene hierarchies – remove the default Main Camera from scene templates; all cameras come from view layers instantiated at runtime
- The `ICameraStack` composes view layer cameras: first registered = Base, rest = Overlay
- Do not search the scene for cameras; the camera stack is populated explicitly when view layers initialize

## Pattern

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD – camera comes from view layer prefab, registered via ICameraStack
_cameraStack.Register(_view.Camera);

// ❌ BAD – searching scene for cameras
var cameras = Object.FindObjectsByType<Camera>(...);
```
